<P>We have a machine for painting cubes. It is supplied with three different 
colors: blue, red and green. Each face of the cube gets one of these colors. The 
cube's faces are numbered as in Figure 1. 
<P>
<P><IMG height=240 alt=picture21 src="253img1.gif" width=255 
align=bottom> 
<P>
<P>
<P>Figure 1. 
<P>Since a cube has 6 faces, our machine can paint a face-numbered cube in <IMG 
height=15 alt=tex2html_wrap_inline126 src="253img2.gif" width=64 
align=bottom> different ways. When ignoring the face-numbers, the number of 
different paintings is much less, because a cube can be rotated. See example 
below. We denote a painted cube by a string of 6 characters, where each 
character is a <TT>b</TT>, <TT>r</TT>, or <TT>g</TT>. The <IMG height=15 
alt=tex2html_wrap_inline128 src="253img3.gif" width=17 align=bottom> 
character ( <IMG height=25 alt=tex2html_wrap_inline130 
src="253img4.gif" width=68 align=middle> ) from the left gives the 
color of face <I>i</I>. For example, Figure 2 is a picture of <TT>rbgggr</TT> 
and Figure 3 corresponds to <TT>rggbgr</TT>. Notice that both cubes are painted 
in the same way: by rotating it around the vertical axis by 90 <IMG height=6 
alt=tex2html_wrap_inline134 src="253img5.gif" width=5 align=bottom> 
, the one changes into the other. 
<P><IMG height=282 alt=tex2html_wrap138 src="253img6.gif" width=257 
align=bottom> <IMG height=282 alt=tex2html_wrap140 src="253img7.gif" 
width=257 align=bottom> 
<H2><FONT color=#0070e8><A 
name=SECTION0001001000000000000000>Input</A></FONT></H2>
<P>The input of your program is a textfile that ends with the standard 
end-of-file marker. Each line is a string of 12 characters. The first 6 
characters of this string are the representation of a painted cube, the 
remaining 6 characters give you the representation of another cube. Your program 
determines whether these two cubes are painted in the same way, that is, whether 
by any combination of rotations one can be turned into the other. (Reflections 
are not allowed.) 
<P>
<H2><FONT color=#0070e8><A 
name=SECTION0001002000000000000000>Output</A></FONT></H2>
<P>The output is a file of boolean. For each line of input, output contains 
<TT>TRUE</TT> if the second half can be obtained from the first half by rotation 
as describes above, <TT>FALSE</TT> otherwise. 
<P>
<H2><FONT color=#0070e8><A name=SECTION0001003000000000000000>Sample 
Input</A></FONT></H2>
<P><PRE>rbgggrrggbgr
rrrbbbrrbbbr
rbgrbgrrrrrg</PRE>
<P>
<H2><FONT color=#0070e8><A name=SECTION0001004000000000000000>Sample 
Output</A></FONT></H2>
<P><PRE>TRUE
FALSE
FALSE</PRE>
